            <title>[ENTESB-3148] Camel pooled threads never die when defined in SwitchYard</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ENTESB-3148</link>
                <project id="12314570" key="ENTESB">JBoss Fuse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SwitchYard/Camel users wish to make use of a custom thread pool to handle Wiretap messages.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;They find the thread pool works as they would like, but there is a complication.  The threads never seem to go away, even when the application that defined the custom pool is undeployed.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;(As observed in Fuse Service Works 6.0GA).  Please make sure this is not present in Fuse 6.2.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
